summary:
Dentinal hypersensitivity commonly follows periodontal surgery because of exposed root surfaces. Desensitizing pastes are effective treatments to reduce sensitivity shortly after removing a periodontal dressing.

\boxed{C}

The summary focuses only on clinically significant facts related directly to minimizing sensitivity right after dressings are removed—specifically identifying dentin exposure as cause and recommending desensitizing paste as an appropriate intervention based on current guidance. This aligns precisely with patient-centered management during early recovery phases without including unrelated or delayed interventions like plaque control.

